employees   website corporatearcelormittalcom arcelormittal sa french pronunciation ​aʁsəlɔʁmiˈtal is a luxembourgbased multinational steel manufacturing corporation headquartered in boulevard d’avranches luxembourg it was formed in  from the takeover and merger of arcelor by mittal steel arcelormittal is the worlds largest steel producer with an annual crude steel production of  million tons as of update it is ranked  in the  fortune global  ranking of the worlds biggest corporations contents  history   formation and scalebacks   losses and senegal agreement   price fixing convictions   recent acquisitions  products and activities  company structure  predecessor companies  board of directors  employees  facilities  headquarters and offices  major plant locations  see also  references  external links historyedit  formation and scalebacksedit arcelormittal was created by the takeover of western european steel maker arcelor spain france and luxembourg by indianowned multinational steel maker mittal steel in  at a cost of € per share approximately  billion total mittal steel launched a hostile takeover bid which replaced a previous planned merger between arcelor and severstal which had lacked sufficient shareholder approval the resulting merged business was named arcelormittal and was headquartered in luxembourg the resulting firm produced approximately  of the worlds steel and was by far the worlds largest steel company total revenues in  were  billion the company earned revenues of  billion in  by february  the company had  employees in  countries in october  the market capitalisation of arcelormittal was over  billion after peaking at  billion in september  at the end of  the company reported operating income of around  billion in december  arcelormittal announced several plant closings including the bethlehem steel plant in lackawanna new york and ltv steel in hennepin illinoiscitation needed after purchase of kryvorizhstal ukraines largest steel producer employmen