ximately  billion total mittal steel launched a hostile takeover bid which replaced a previous planned merger between arcelor and severstal which had lacked sufficient shareholder approval the resulting merged business was named arcelormittal and was headquartered in luxembourg the resulting firm produced approximately  of the worlds steel and was by far the worlds largest steel company total revenues in  were  billion the company earned revenues of  billion in  by february  the company had  employees in  countries in october  the market capitalisation of arcelormittal was over  billion after peaking at  billion in september  at the end of  the company reported operating income of around  billion in december  arcelormittal announced several plant closings including the bethlehem steel plant in lackawanna new york and ltv steel in hennepin illinoiscitation needed after purchase of kryvorizhstal ukraines largest steel producer employment was scaled back from  employees to citation needed  losses and senegal agreementedit in  the companys operating income had fallen to  billion with sales down  percent from the year earlier and income down  percent as steel prices slumped in  the company began curtailing its european production to match the reduced demand for steel it also sold skyline steel and astralloy to a rival nucor for  million on  january  the stainless steel division split off as a new company aperamcitation needed as of update due to overcapacity and reduced demand in europe it had idled  of  blast furnaces in october  it permanently shut down two blast furnaces at florange france on october   the company reported a thirdquarter loss of  million as compared to a  million profit for the same period a year ago citing the slow down in chinas economy in  arcelormittal had  billion of debt in january  arcelormittal bid  billion to acquire thyssenkrupp ags rolling mill in calvert alabama united states on february   thyssenkrupp sold their calvert carbon steel facility to arcelormittal and nippon steel for  billion as a new joint venture the facility was renamed amns calvert through the  joint partnership with nippon steel  sumitomo metal corp the firm also entered into a  billion contract to develop an iron ore deposit in senegal this included construction of a  km  mi railway line after stalling on the contract and failing to build according to schedule the government of senegal sued in september  the government of senegal won a court case before an international tribunal to rescind a  billion deal with arcelormittal after the company suspended work on an iron ore mine in the country in june  the international chamber of commerces arbitration court in paris awarded senegal  million dealing with price and demand fluctuations in the steel market from  to  arcelormittal restructured its european division by reducing employee numbers and closing plants in may  arcelormittal citing economic selfinterest declared its opposition to sanctions on russia as of june  arcelormittal accounted for  percent of world steel production after being shut out of the chinese steel industry in  along with other foreign companies in  the company announced it was planning new plants in china in  the company had an annual crude steel production of  million tons  price fixing convictionsedit following an investigation first launched in  in august  the south african competition commission found the company guilty of price fixing arcelormittal was fined us million and as part of the settlement also agreed to invest r billion in capital over five years according to the findings the firm had been part of a  steel member groups nicknamed club zürich that later became known as club europe between january  and september  the companies fixed the market prices and exchanged confidential corporate information according to a european union commission vicepresident it was amazing how the cartel abused nearly the entire european construction market for such a long time and for such a vital product fines were particularly high for the firm owing to two prior convictionscitation needed  recent acquisitionsedit in  the company had a net loss of  billion between february  and february  share value dropped  making the company the worst performer in the ftseurofirst index the ceo said the company had performed poorly in  due to chinese exports depressing prices early in  the company announced it had raised  billion in new investment capital to help reduce debt to  billion of debt in early  the company also announced a program to boost core profit by  billion by  through a mixture of costcutting increased production and a focus on highervalue forms of steel chairman lakshmi mittal announced doubled earnings the following year in may  along with the increase in capital the company also sold its  stake in gestamp automacion for  million with the goal of reducing arcelormittals debt to less than  billion by february  the company made about  of the worlds steel it ranked th in the  fortune global  ranking of the worlds biggest corporations in february  arcelormittal announced its first annual profits in five years in february  arcelormittal and votorantim announced plans to combine their long steel operations in brazil under the deal votorantim siderurgia became a subsidiary of arcelormittal brasil in late may  arcelormittal and the steel authority of india ltd sail agreed on preliminary terms to form a  million joint venture to export a fifth of the autograde steel made by the venture in march  the company proposed a new usd  billion steel project in karnataka after entering into a pact with the karnataka government in february  in april  sanjeev guptas liberty house group announced it had agreed to acquire arcelormittals georgetown steelworks in south carolina it is ranked  in the  fortune global  ranking of the worlds biggest corporations by march  arcelormittal was leading a consortium bidding for ilva an italian company ilva owns the taranto steelworks in southern italy which has europes largest steel output the steelworks had been accused of toxic emissions linked to local cancer rates and had been nationalized by the government years prior the buyers were the am investco consortium which beyond arcelormittal included marcegaglia and banca intesa sanpaolo in may  arcelormittal was announced as the preferred bidder over a different consortium led by jsw steel after it was able to pledge a production increase and guarantee employment levels the final decision was waiting on italy’s ministry of economic development on june   arcelormittal won approval to purchase ilva for € billion in its bid am investco had pledged to make investments into ilva of €bn until  products and activitiesedit steel being rolled at an acelormittal facility in brazil the company is involved in research and development mining and steel arcelormittal in  produced around  million tons of steel as of may  the company made  unique steel grades for automotive purposes half of which were introduced since  among the steel varieties are usibor  which the company announced in june  and released later that year upon release the highstrength automotive steel was said to be about onethird stronger than other steels then available for carmaking company structureedit lakshmi mittal owner of mittal steel is the chairman and ceo his family owns  of the shares and voting shares in the company after a  billion rights issue earlier in april  the company by the  april  had a share value of  million euros distributed in  shares predecessor companiesedit acquired by mittal steel company international steel group acquired  bethlehem steel  united states acquired  isg weirton steel  united states acquired  ltvsteel  united states acquired  republic steel  united states acquired  jones and laughlin steel  united states acquired  acme steel  chicago us acquired  ispat international acquired  arcelormittal kryvyi rih  ukraine acquired  acquired 